title: Print, "Design for Cartouche with Fountain and Sea Putti, in Livre Nouveau de Morceaux de Fantaisie (New Book of Works of Fantasy)", 1738 and 1745
medium: Engraving and etching on laid paper
signed: lower left: F. de. Cuvilliés. In. et. del.; lower right: CA. de Lespilliez Sc.
inscribed: Inscribed, in plate, lower center: C. P. S. C. M.
creditline: Purchased for the Museum by the Advisory Council
description: In landscape, large rocaille formation on ground, merman putto holds spear and with right hand gestures toward cartouche, framed by rocaille design depicting spears. On right, columned structure. Above, merman putto sits atop fountain structure in rocaille motif; above this, putto sits holding vase spewing water and trellis-like element reaching to the right structure, with hanging putto.
